  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Describe the feature you would like\n\nDescribed by @mds1 \r\n\r\n> We can consider excluding special foundry addresses from the fuzz dictionary. This would be all addresses that behave differently in foundry than they do on live chains, which includes:\r\n> \r\n>  - VM address\r\n>  - Console address\r\n>  - Are there others?\r\n> \r\n> Create2Deployer and precompiles are valid inputs an attacker can pass in real life, so we wouldn't want to exclude those.\r\n\r\n- VM Address: `0x7109709ECfa91a80626fF3989D68f67F5b1DD12D` ([ref](https://github.com/dapphub/dapptools/blob/master/src/hevm/README.md#cheat-codes))\r\n- Console address: `0x000000000000000000636F6e736F6c652e6c6f67` ([ref](https://github.com/foundry-rs/forge-std/blob/5bafa16b4a6aa67c503d96294be846a22a6f6efb/src/console2.sol#L10))\n\n### Additional context\n\nhttps://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/issues/3625",
